values:
I feel like I'm just falling and spinning quickly down a bottomless empty hole.
I have no clue why I am where I am.
I'm not happy.
People talk, and I hear.
They don't want anything to do with me.
I'm different.
I want out.
I'm not even looking forward to my birthday because I know something will go horribly wrong.
People already have forgotten that my birthday is coming up, I don't remind them.
Why do I have to be surrounded by who want nothing to do with me on my birthday.
If Trevor didn't have something planed for me on my birthday I'd go to Atlanta and be with my family.
I miss Atlanta.
I miss the thought of safety.
I miss acceptance.
I miss simplicity.
I miss freedom of speech.
I miss cynical bitches like me.
I miss the old me.
I've lost my smile and I have no clue where it went.
What the hell is happiness anyway?
Is this the way it's gonna be the rest of my life?
If so, I have nothing to look forward to.
Time to find that secluded cabin in the woods to lock myself in and throw away the key.
I guess I'm gonna go look for one.
I'm back in Cochran.....and I'm home sick

Holy Hell! 

It's been a pretty long time since I've posted...I even forgot I had a LJ! Wow

Anyway, my winter break has been wonderful! Very relaxing...nothing exciting really happened, but you know sometimes people need down time. I've spent most of the break with my family. Yes that may seem lame and childish, but I'm so grateful for every second that I got to spent with them and I love them. I'm gonna miss them all so much and I know the first few weeks are gonna be hard for me and for them as well. Dad's been trying his hardest to keep me home as long as possible. I went from planing on going back to Cochran before New Years to waiting till last minute the day before classes start. I'm just soaking up every drama free, worry free, and judgement free second I have left. 

I'm so nervous about this coming semester...I have to do extra well because I plan on transferring to Georgia State as soon as possible. I'm ready to leave Cochran. Coming back to Atlanta and hanging out with old friends made me realize that I don't fit in in Cochran because people down there don't get me...in Atlanta I feel like I can relate to so many more people. So I think this coming semester will be my last if I can improve my grades. 

Cochran won't miss me and I have a feeling I won't miss it much either. But I'll keep in touch with the people that I love. But until I mature more and can handle rejection better I don't think Cochran is the right place for me. A sheltered city girl has no business in a place like Cochran...too bad it took me so long to see that. 

Oh well....rant over

Peace Up...A-Town Down

I've never in my life ever felt so alone and lost as I do now. I feel like my life is spinning out of control and there is nothing I can do about it. I'm under a microscope here, every mistake I make is picked apart and criticized and I'm sick of it. Nothing I do seems right, I can't please anyone! Am I that flawed? Or is it the fact that I live in a fucking butt crack redneck retarded town? I'm clueless I have no idea what I have done to disserve this. I feel unwanted and unloved....I'm disgusted with the person who I have become down here, so much so it's hard getting out of bed. I don't wanna do anything anymore because no matter what I do it's wrong! I could go out and cure cancer but the people here will hate me because I didn't cure AIDS. Hell I could feed every hungry mouth in the world and people here would get pissed because I didn't invite them over to dinner once. Some bullshit like that. Whatever happened to forgiveness? Do people here not believe in that anymore? I don't know how many more times I'll have to say it but I'M SORRY! I'll be apologizing to people here till the second I die, my last words will probably be "I'm sorry" I'm mostly sorry to myself for putting up with this bullshit as long as I have. I wish I hadn't signed up for spring classes because I'm ready to go; I'm ready to put this shit in my past. I'm ready for this town and almost everyone in it to be a memory. I'm ready to find some open arms somewhere, some place safe, some place where I can be myself...Good, Bad, happy, sad, grumpy. Whatever and not have to worry about being accepted. I just wanna move on and continue to grow freely. I'm not a bad person am I?

Or else you'll end up like me last night: Drunk as fuck and locked out of my apartment. Last night as I reached my drinking destination, I realized I didn't have my keys to get back into my apartment........what did I do? Got drunk as fuck and said "I'll worry about that later." Well later came and began to worry I'd be locked out in the cold. Jason Wright drove me home and told me he'd help me break in. I stumbled up the stairs and started to turn the door knob and bang my shoulder up against the door....after seeing that yes indeed the door was still locked, I made my way to Erika's window as Jason looked at the other windows. I took the screen off and said a silent prayer that the window is un-locked and sure enough, it was. I got a boost from Jason and crawled into Erika's room. I ran to the door and opened it so I could thank Jason and give him a hug. It was a very fun night I must say.
Bethany and Amelia shocked the hell out of me with a visit to see me perform closing night of the play....Really it was an awesome surprise!

I'm sick 
Allergies. My nose is runny and my throat is scratchy, not to mention I just feel yucky 
But on a good note! The other night I was chilling here at the apt in Erika's room after practice and the doorbell rang. Erika went and answered the door while I stayed behind in her room. Erika comes back to the room with a weird look on her face, like she was trying to be serious but couldn't help but smile a little bit. "It's for you" Erika says and first thought I have is Aw fuck either it's the Mexicans or this guy I use to work with back in Atlanta who has been semi stocking me lately. I asked Erika who is it? But she wouldn't tell me....so I'm like this can't be good. 
I walk out of Erika's room through the hall and into the living room to see Mike standing there! I felt my heart skip a beat! It was a total surprise and a great one at that. It was so sweet of him to just drop by to say hi, and it made me feel so good. 
He's such a sweet considerate MAN....yes finally a MAN....no more immature little burn out boys for me. The 7 year age gap doesn't bother me much; I just hope it doesn't bother him. I try to act mature...at least for my age that is. 
I just feel so good when I'm around Mike, I feel safe and like I can be myself without having to worry about my acne infested skin. The first time he saw me...the real me....I had no make up on and he looked me in the eye and told me I was beautiful....I might be ignorant when it comes to the subject of relationships, but that's a good thing right? Like that has to mean something right? I mean you don't just go around and tell random people you meet for the first time that they are beautiful without meaning it am I right? I just don't wanna get my hopes up, I want him to be more than a boy who wants to get in my pants....anyway, I'm just hoping I can hang out with him some this weekend...we'll see.

Unhappy.....no.....more like depressed

I am so full of sadness right now...I'm overflowing and about to burst.

I hate who I am right now

I hate how I look

I hate how I act

I hate how no one here seems to like me

I hate how I don't fit in

I hate how it's like I'm back in middle school...sticking out like a soar thumb

I hate how I feel like I need a guy to make me feel good about myself

I hate how it feels like no matter how much I hate myself....I can't seem to change anything. Like I am stuck in a position of pure loneliness and bitterness.

I hate putting on an act

I hate feeling fake

I hate that Erika has to put up with me

I hate that I feel so guilty

I hate....I hate all this hate

Something odd has happened.....

....you know that saying "When one door shuts....another one opens"?

Well I had a door shut the other day when a certain someone stopped acknowledging my presence and stopped wanting to be with me. He never called me anymore, he never returned my calls he just ignored me...I could have walked in naked and he would have shrugged it off. These past two weeks have felt like rock bottom in the love life department. I mean maybe I'm over analyzing or over exasperating or fuck doing both. But I mean I had given up on men for the time being. I really stopped dressing up and looking pretty I didn't care. 

Then the night before last. Erika and I were watching Garden State when Perkins and his roommate Mike came over for a visit. I looked like shit so I didn't look at the guys....I just kept my head turned looking towards the TV. It started to get late and I decided to take a shower and call it a night. I said goodnight to everyone and told Mike it was nice to finally meet him...and then retreated to the bathroom and took a nice long shower expecting to go right to bed. I finished my shower...walked to my room rapped in a towel and started getting dressed in my PJs. I heard a knock. I thought it was Erika so jokingly I shouted "I'M NAKED!!!!"........silence.......5 minutes later........another knock. I opened the door wearing my big baggy t-shirt and soccer shorts with soaking wet hair and NO MAKE UP to find Mike, Perkins roommate standing there. I was totally shocked and embarrassed that I turned away. "Hey, I was wondering if I could get your phone number?" he asked me.......shocked......I grabbed the closest piece of paper and a huge sharpie and wrote my number down. I did all this without looking at him.....he noticed this and asked me about it.....I told him I didn't want him to see me like this. But then he said "Why? Eliza, you have THE MOST beautiful eyes I've ever seen and I think you look fine." I stared at him in disbelief....blushed.....then thanked him. He asked if I was doing anything the next night and of course I said no. He told me he'd call me and we would hang out.....and I said fine. He left and I sat down and tried to collect my thoughts on what just happened. Then it struck me! Since I've been having trouble with a certain someone and have been feeling really down about myself......I thought that maybe Erika and Perkins put Mike up to it. Erika came in a little later and I questioned her.... 
"Did you put him up to it?" 
"Who up to what?" 
"Mike, did you put him up to it?"
"No...what?...why? What happened?"
"He asked me out"
"REALLY??????"
"Yeah...did you and Perkins put him up to it?"
"No! I had no clue he was going to ask you out! That's awesome!"
"Really?"
*SILINCE*
"He was probably highly intoxicated"
"No he wasn't!"
"Really? You sure?"
"Yeah!"
"..........well damn!"

He came over last night and we hung out. Watched a movie and talked. The other man saw me with Mike and was really pissed. I don't know how to feel about that. Part of me wants to shout...."You had your chance! You blew it!" but then I feel guilty...like maybe I should give him another chance. I don't want people to think that I'm trying to flaunt that another guy likes me in his face.... but then again....knowing that he is pissed does make me feel pretty good. 

I'm torn in half

I'm a weakling

I'm sorry

I'm lost

I'm clueless has to what to do and what to feel

I rejoice a little and die a little at the same time

Then I eat my ramen noodles and worry some more about my audition

and I change the subject

as Bob Barker talks on the TV screen

and I'm still as a loss for words.......

I had a dream the other night that I was a mermaid. It was a beautiful dream. But I had to know what dreaming about mermaids meant. I looked it up and found out that it means bad luck in love life.....well fuck

Yes sir...I am in Cock-Town once again. This time I am living in an apartment (College Station) with my best good friend Erika. Things are fine, I guess. I mean life is a whole new ball game now that I live off campus. Instead of feeling disconnected with the whole world when I was living in a dorm, I now feel disconnected from the college world. I don't really feel like a normal college student....I've been one before and I didn't like the way it felt. I feel more grown up now. I have bills to pay, I have to get my own food and I have to find mature ways of entertaining myself. For example; because I have no cable or internet at the apartment I have to read or "Study" two things I never did when living in the dorm. And you can look at that any which way you like....either I'm having less fun or I've finally grown up. Either way I am a new person, or at least I feel like one. 

Boys my handling of boys is still them same, I am still a coward. Bill and I don't communicate. We both like each other, but then we think that the other one hates the other and gets discouraged and we avoid each other. But then we have our good days, where we both get kisses and get to hang out together. So far since being back we've had one good day together and I'm pretty sure Bill's attraction towards me was enhanced by him being pretty damn drunk. He couldn't keep his hands off of me and I liked that. But I had to ignore the beer breath which I have grown use to. But I don't know what to do anymore. I don't want a boyfriend to be drunk all the time, but again I don't want a boyfriend who doesn't even notice me. So I'm in a rut. 

I'm pretty lonely. But depression hasn't sunk in yet. I still am getting my feet wet and finding my routine. I'm gonna start going to the gym and a few other things like that. But I'm running out of things to say.......I think I'm gonna wait a bit then go to the dinning hall and get something to eat. Erika is going to be in Warner Robins all night. I'm gonna be alone tonight in the apartment. This is when having a caring boyfriend would come in handy.

I'm in the school library and I have a class at 11 that I need to jet to. But yes I'm in Cock-town. I'm living in a Apartment with my pal Erika...I'm taking 12 credit hours. I have three classes Mondays and Wednesdays and two classes Tuesdays and Thursdays....
Erika works in the day and goes to class at night. I'm lonely. Boys suck. I'm gonna be late to my next class if I don't jet now...I'll try and update later.....PEACE!
...I'm heartbroken and alone in Cochran! PAR-TAY!

I'm sick
my allergies have been acting up....I think I must be allergic to something in the air or around my house, or maybe the ADD weather might be causing my body to be outta whack.
I have a little bit of everything. Soar throat, sneezing, coughing, and up-set stomach. It's not cool. But I'm trying not to let this blah ugh feeling stop me from getting out and enjoying this summer.
I've made an appointment to get a 30 minute facial which is heaven...and I've been shopping like hell for stuff for my new apt. I now LOVE Bed Bath and Beyond! I'm so thankful that one opened up close by. ALSO....a Target and a Starbucks opened up close by in the same shopping complex.....I love Starbucks! God I sound like such a city girl...woohoo...that's what I am.
Anyway, back to being sick...I'm pretty drugged up right now. I took two benedrils so I'm sleepy, but I also drunk a whole mug of coffee so I'm awake. I look like something out of cartoon. One second I'm dozing off...the next second the coffee kicks in and I'm alert. My ears are clogged up....I have my TV at full blast like a 90-year-old. I'm so forgetful right now. I've forgotten to call Stacie back...I feel bad for that.....I've forgotten to do a bunch of other stuff too...I'd list them but I've forgotten what they are. ....Maybe I should take a long hot shower.....uh oh....dozing off now.........................zzzzzzzzzzz
I need a craft project to do
I wanna go to an art store today
I need to lose weight, maybe if I look sexier Bill will call me more often
I can't wait till I get a faical and then go to the dermotologyst
I am a fat blob
I hate that there are people I hate getting MySpaces and adding me even though all last semester they contributed to the spreding of rummors of me
A guy that I met in person via American singles got a MYspace added me and wants to see me again! I totally stoped talking to him 'cause I wasn't interested in him anymore....you'd think he'd get the hint....maybe if he sees me in person he'll change his mind and leave me alone
My driving lessions start on the 29th...I'm scared
Grrrrr all I can think of is how much weight I've gained
Okay...enough of this...I'm just gonna drink my diet coke and watch the Price is Right.

Don't point fingers till you know all the facts.....

It looks as if I'm not going to be going to Cochran this weekend. There is a major conflict amongst friends down there. I hate when friends fight. You sit back and watch/hear this happening and you feel useless because there is nothing you can do. You don't wanna take sides in fear that you'll piss everyone off. So here I sit...wondering what can be done.

The point is...this conflict is silly in my eyes. I was THERE I saw that NOTHING happened. People who were not there are pointing fingers and taking sides without hearing both sides. Don't jump to conclusions....It takes two to tango. I don't wanna say much more because this isn't any of my business and should be amongst the three main people involved. I had a great weekend. I got to go home yay! I went to the Inman park festival that I never miss. It was grand! I got to see some old Elementary school friends of mine and chat it up with them. The festival has one of the coolest and craziest parades in the country and this year was no exception. There were drag queens and one Elvis look-a-like that pointed to ME and shook his hips at me, I felt my cheeks turn bright red and I giggled. I felt so at home for the first time in such a long time, yes being surrounded by drag queens helps me feel at home. But I had so much fun! A good friend of mine bought me this great green hat that truly is one of a kind and I'll treasure it forever! There was so much art at the festival that gave me a good idea, if acting doesn't work out, I wanna open up an art gallery for really avant-garde artists that would be super cool. 

          Even though I was home just for the weekend, it was still long enough to feel somewhat at peace for the first time in a long time. I was away from all the drama at MGC and away from the ignorant people that go to this college. Even though I'm not directly involved in the drama (For once) I'm still affected by it 'cause my friends are dealing with it. All this drama has caused me to see a person in a whole new light. It's really disappointing, because I now see that this person is not as laid-back and free spirited as they appeared to be. You can't say you're not taking sides if you refuse to hear the other side of the story. I believe this person is being totally un-reasonable, although it's not really my place to say so, I still am gonna say it, because even though this event doesn't evolve me, it evolves my friends and I don't like seeing people hurt them for no reason. Fuck this drama and fuck un-reasonable people. 
        One more week till I leave this hell hole for a summer, yay! I'm gonna miss all my friends dearly, but I know I'll see them this summer some how. I just hope I don't lose touch with any of them. This summer is gonna be pretty okay, for some reason I have a really positive feeling about it and that's not normal for me, miss pessimist. I think the main contribution to my positive outlook is the knowledge that I'm gonna go a summer without seeing some of the cheep sluts that I despise more then anything in the world. I hope they all learn a really good lesion over the summer, stay the fuck away from my male friends and if they cause any of them grief, I'll fuck'em up. 
        A great weekend ahead of me yay! Camp-out Thursday night, Harris cook out, ENCORE party and finally drum circle in Atlanta!!! Should be loads of fun. Well....I'd write more but I'm afraid I've bored y'all enough with my ranting, so I'll end this post now. Everyone have a good one! Much love to all!

....Have you ever done soemthing that at the time seemed okay, but you look back and you think "What the fuck was I thinking?" Yeah well....That's me again, that's the way I feel right now. I've done something and now I regret it and I must face the consiquinces. I don't wanna say what it was, 'cause I'm asshamed of it, it's nothing really bad, just not good. But it has to do with how I don't know what I want. So yeah, I dunno what to do, just hope for the best I guess.
I have a choice to make. Should I go home this weekend for the Inman Park festivel that I never ever miss, or should I stay here and spend what little time I have left with my friends? Right now I'm leaning towards going home. Unless someone wants to plan a trip to the beach or fishing, then I really have no reason to stay. I'm almost always bored here and that makes me depressed, so yeah right now I'm thinking that I'm gonna go home. I'm gonna start packing up shit in my dorm and take it all home with me this weekend. I can't believe that I'm almost done with my first year at college, it doesn't seem real at all. It feels like just yesterday I was moving into Willham scared to death and sad as hell. I hate looking back on those first two months when I moved down here, they were two of the most depressing months of my life! But yeah.....whatever.

I can't wait till the drum circle in Atlanta on the 30th! It's gonna be a blast! I'm gonna take all the MGC people to Little 5 points and show them around, OMG it's gonna be great! We're gonna be hippies all day long, woo hoo! So yeah, nothing going on with me right now I'm bored so I'm gonna find something to do. Much love to all!

I feel like I'm headed towards a mental breakdown. I've never been so stressed, so tired,  so unsure of myself, and so deeply deeply sad. This play is driving me crazy. Normally when a play is almost over I'm sad about it, but now I've never wanted a play to be over and done with. The only good thing about the play is I get to hang out with Erika (Us being in the play together and brought us closer together and I'm so grateful for that) also I have a beautiful costume that makes me feel somewhat glamorous. 
It's hard to really describe the state of mind I'm trapped in right now. Totally stuck between a rock and a hard place. I was hoping being in this play would pull me closer to other people, one in particular, but really this play seems to be pulling us farther apart. I think this person is really starting to see the nitty gritty of me and thinks that there is no way in hell they will be able to handle this side of me. In reality, this side of me is a side I rarely like to show; therefore I avoid it at all times. I hate being stressed, tired and grumpy, but sometimes it's just so un-avoidable. 
This person last night whispered something to me during the run-threw about my dancing skills. I know they didn't mean it a harmful way, but it still really hurt my feelings. I felt like an ignorant child and more so coming from that certain person. I'm really really sensitive when it comes to certain things, I put up a tough care free attitude, but really it's so easy to hurt me. Things rarely just roll off my back. I just wish more then anything this person could understand me or at least try to. I'm so complicated, I know that, but God try to see me, look at me! I'm so tempted to ask this person what they truly think of me, but I'm so scared to hear the answer. If they something bad then rightfully so I'll be badly hurt, but if they something really nice then I'll be left questioning a lot of things. Really I'm wishing that I didn't get so fixated on certain things or certain people. But this person is like none I have ever met before in my life! This is something new and exciting that I want to explore, I wanna be like this person. I wanna study this person. Is this love? Ooooooo frightening word, love, just saying it then sent shivers down my spine. I know when its lust and the feeling I have is not lust. Because....well.....I just want to be around this person because this person strikes a cored in me when they are paying attention that makes me feel like the luckiest person in the world. A smile from this person in my direction turns my cheeks into a flaming red color. A compliment makes me feel so humble. A hug makes me feel important. A touch makes me feel....like butter. How pathetic am I? lol. If I don't become famous, most likely I'll become a stocker.
Anyway, I'm just so madly in need of a break and possibly a lot of time away from this person so that I can reevaluate my feeling and attitude towards them and maybe just maybe they'll be doing the same. But yes, a vacation sounds so lovely right now. A day at the beach is like a wet dream lol for me right now lol. But right now, I'd settle for a day of lying around my home and watching movies. 
Well, I need to go do some laundry before Ikner comes into town and then take shower. I wanna look good for him and for the play. So yeah, I'm done with running off at the mouth for now. Wish me luck for tonight and I shall talk to you all later!

God, I'd give anything to have had our conversation be a better one. I wish I hadn't been so stubborn and jealous, just swallowed my pride and been happy. It's a wake up call, you never know if a conversation with a person could be the last one you ever have with that person. So now I'm gonna try and be nicer to people because right now I feel like I'm a horrible person. First Amy gets a brain tumor and I was a horrible roommate to her and now Michael is near death and I was a horrible friend to him. I feel like I'm being punished. Michael doesn't need to be the one near death he doesn't. Sometimes I wish I could take his spot. God, I wish I could see him and talk to him. I feel like I could pick up the phone dial his number and he'll pick up. All last night when I was sitting in the waiting room, I kept getting this feeling that Michael would burst through the doors and say one of his trademark lines like "Do It!" or "Alllllllll Riiiiiiiiiiiiiight" 
I'm gonna go back to the hospital today after classes are done. Erika told me she'd drive me. I'm hopping they got him stable enough to where they can life flight him safely to Emory. I know I'd feel so much better if he were at Emory where something like this is like a walk in the park for them. 
I know Michael is a strong person and he's fighting. I hope he knows that he like 15 close friends waiting at the Hospital for him till 2:30am. I hope he knows that we love him and admire him so much. Erika and I have been saying the rosary. We went in the Hospital chapel twice and did the rosary. When we were done we got some good news that his fever had gone down, we'd like to think that faith had a hand in that.
Well please everyone keep Michael in your thoughts and prayers. We all love him and there will be a lot of devastated people if he doesn't pull through. The world will be missing a truly talented and sweet person.
